T~L~735~-535~0~#0000FF~~9pt~undefined~undefined~~comment~The isolator requires a minimum

handle the other 10ma thus we need a
500 ohm resistor hear and a 270 ohm
resistor on the LDO~1~start~gge53389~0~pinpart

T~L~-635~1595~0~#0000FF~~9pt~~~~comment~Schottky Diodes for protecting
The STM32 in the condition that
the switch is in Bipolar Mode and
the stm32 ADC is in an off (high
impedance) state. In this state
the negative voltage on the bottom side
of the resistor divider in bipolar mode
could cause a negative voltage at the
stm32 input~1~start~gge64619~0~pinpart

T~L~-640~-135~0~#0000FF~~9pt~~~~comment~We want a voltage/capacitive divider with a gain of 
0.82 in order attenuate
the signal before it gets to the op amp as the op
amp is only -2.75 to 2.75
 
This will also help with current limiting as the op
amp will clamp it's inputs to 10ma. The parasitic
capacitance of the circuit is around 13pF depending
on the channel and trace lengths. Thus we need to form
the other side of the capacitive divider with a 56pF
cap and a 0.75pF to 1.5pF cap to GND for tuning 
(sharpening the edges)~1~start~gge65542~0~pinpart
T~L~295~500~0~#0000FF~~9pt~~~~comment~Series resistance in the case of the op amp\nstruggling to drive a capacitive load.~1~start~gge73682~0~pinpart
